staticData.msgToolTipAssets: An asset is a resource that a company owns that provides economic value as reported on the balance sheet. This includes cash, equipment, property, rights to anything that a company can expect to generate revenue or reduce expenses.
staticData.msgToolTipGrossProfit: Gross profit is the total profit obtained by a business. It is the difference between net sales or revenue and the cost of goods sold.
staticData.msgToolTipIncorporated: The year which the company is incorporated under the law of a specific jurisdiction, as recorded in the document filed with the registry or a similar body.
staticData.msgToolTipKeyPrincipal: The person identified as a key stakeholder of the business or organization by the local registry or other official sources. The key stakeholder can be a person or an organization.
staticData.msgToolTipYearFounded: The date the entity chooses to claim as its established date.
